caption: Come on, the BEST!
Good but pricey.
Cutest little sandwich shop and a popular one too. Skip the wait by ordering ahead on Seamless or place your order and come back for pickup.

This place is outstanding. Absolutely delicious sandwiches. Don't come here looking for value - it's gonna run you $15 for a sandwich and they're pretty small. Just know that you're treating yourself to something you'll really enjoy.

ALWAYS STOCKED UP WITH WHAT YOU NEED. LINES ARE NEVER TO LONG. PRICES ARE JUST A LITTLE BIT PRICEY BUT ALSO VERY CLEAN STAFF IS ALWAYS FRIENDLY AND HELPFUL ***** This is where I always do my grocery shopping My one problem here is sometimes the meat goes bad quickly
Dope sandwich
Probably the best sandwiches in NYC! Beautifully crafted. Classic yet creative. Delicious.

The Droopy was really good! The main problem is the wait, try to order ahead or be ready to wait 30 min at peak hour.  I’m always a bit skeptical when I see a lot of ingredients stacked between bread, and their sandwiches can’t be considered light by any standard, but their combinations are quite original, and every time the meat was tender, and the bread lighter than I expected.
This place should be a 24/7 operation, maybe the best sandwiches in the city
Used to be an occasional spot for me pre-COVID... now I come here about 3 times a week!

Best sandwiches in the neighborhood. I would only say that because you wait outside to pick up your sandwich to either call ahead or ask how long it's going to take to get your food. Waiting outside in 20 degree weather for 25 minutes is rough. But it was totally worth it.
One of my favorite sandwich spots. Everything is in point.
Good sandwiches but if you're looking for a great Italian Combo you gotta go to Esposito's(Court & President) , it's bigger, it tastes much better and it's $4.00 less.
One of my favorite coffee and sandwich place in the area. Always hits the spot!
Creative and tasty sandwiches. Great people run this shop. So good I go through withdrawal. Try every location for something special.
This place is a local staple. Stop by if you’re in the neighborhood!
Best ever.
To enjoy a sandwich and a coffee here is worth it. A very nice place inside and very clean. Very safe for everyone as the staff serves with masks.Thank you Court Street Grocers for nice time here!

a tastee roast beef sandwich was enjoyed along with tastes of a cubano, a very hot split pea soup and a cup of coffee ... staff masked and occupancy diligently adhered to ... greatly enjoyed and amused by pickup window and colorful post it note order system ...
Wonderful people
Best sandwiches in the area. Can recommend anything with the comeback sauce --especially the broc sandwich
Great for breakfast sandwiches
Best. Sandwiches. Ever. Definitely worth the wait.

This place is fabulous!! The staff was very helpful, polite & cheerful. The sandwich (I ordered their take on a Roast Beef hero: The Droopy) was delicious & enough for 2 meals!! I enjoyed the bottled What Cheer!  ginger ale ( ole fashioned taste of real ginger & not like the other watered  down versions you normally get ). I really appreciated that their setup ( Food order prep, customer pickup & payment) was very Covid-19 safe, social distanced & orderly.  I HIGHLY RECOMMEND THEM!!
Friendly service with social distancing.

Some of the best sandwiches in NY. Make sure you order early and online for pickup or local delivery. Personal favorite is the italian combo. But you cannot go wrong. Also have amazing vegetarian options.
Great spot for breakfast sandwiches. The ciabatta rolls are amazing!
Best bfast sandwich ever, great pickup service as well.

People here are split between Rude and no personality to overly nice. I tip them based on the guy with no personality and being rude, but overall the service is between meh and rude. Three other Court streets are fantastic. $0 is my permanent tip here ... But here's another tip, don't be a dry ahole on the phone.
I'm glad that Brooklyn still has a few places you can get a good sandwich.

Sandwiches that will change your life. As a newcomer turned regular, I haven’t had a disappointing bite yet. I’ve brought many friends here and when they leave NYC they still talk about how great their sandwich was! Definitely try the broccoli rueben, uncle chucky or tuna berry. Or anything for that matter.

I heard about this place because of the YouTube channel of Bon Appétit. Finally, after waiting a bit due to COVID-19, my Mom and I adventured into the Red Hook area. Was it worth the 30 minute drive and 30 minute wait for a sandwich? Yes. We had the Tuna Berry and Vegi Delight which we both split. Both delicious in their own way. We also shared their chocolate chip cookie and the orange olive oil cake which was moist, dense and delicious. Highly recommend. Also recommend going to the park down the block to enjoy the sandwich during the pandemic.
I'm not much of a sandwich person, but that was easily one of the best sandwiches I've ever had. I got the vegitalian.
Soooooo good. Great sandwiches, lovely service, and excellent vegetarian options. (the vegetalian is terrific!)
Amazing sandwiches.

Finally made it to this place. Tried the Ollie turkey sandwich which was great. I make some good sandwiches at home, and normally when I do take out I'll doctor it up a bit. I wouldn't change a thing on this sandwhich. The flavors, texture, and sesame roll were all perfect together.  Look forward to trying more things!
I absolutely love the droopy sandwich. It's on really good bread, with roast beef, horseradish, and other yummy stuff. 😍
**Ordered takeout during COVID pandemic  Food *B+B (Scrambled eggs, arugula & bacon on ciabatta roll) - good; nice contrast with all three elements of the sandwich
They have a great COVID pickup process
Excellent sandwiches. With lots of vegetarian options. Grandpa sandwich is highly recommended.

Great and interesting sandwiches. I love their Turkish delight. You really can’t go wrong here. It’s a great sandwich shop and they have amazing chocolate cake and dill pickle chips. I come here every other Sunday for lunch.
Great little sandwich shop. Cool decor and a bit of Peter Falk art, for some good reason.
Got everyting we needs
Very kind and fun staff! Delicious sandwiches. Worth the price. Will be back.

Court Street Grocers is one of the best sandwich shops in the Carroll street area. A great selection of sandwiches with lots and lots options. Thankfully not only did they have gulten y bread, but it tasted like regular bread. 10/10

I’m sure you don’t need me to tell you, but these sandwiches rock. What you may not know is that the coffee they serve is rocket fuel even for a caffeine addict such as myself, personally not a fan of the patty melt, but not worth docking a star, seating is limited be nice and share tables! Great selection of niche grocery items
The Jawn is Great
I ordered two sandwiches, intending to eat a half of each and save the rest for later. Ended up eating both. Jesus they were good. Had the Jawn and the Broccoli Reuben.

Love love love this place! All the sandwiches are super good but my favorite is the VeggItalian!!! It’s delicious and flavorful. Perfect sandwich for a vegetarian. They have a nice selection of drinks too.
clean turkey is one of the best sandwiches ever created, i promise
Sandwiches are only as good as the bread and this place has some really good bread.  Very satisfying 👌
The bread is amazing - seedy, crunchy and fluffy. Favorite sandwich is the Clean Turkey with pickled red onions.
Best sandwiches IN TOWN

Oh baby you, you got what I neeeed. Best sandwich I had in the city and it's not close. Went with the Italian two times and I'm sitting here dreaming of a third as I type. Hype well earned with these guys. Why are you still reading this review? Go, my pretty. Go with god.
Always a great experience when I come (food wise) place is small but food is big love every sandwich I get from here.. machoman is my go to sandwich btw
Flavors are incredible but quantity of meat is lacking on most sandwiches. Italian combo has 1 layer of meat, rueben as well.
The best Turkey sandwich I've ever had!!!!!

Great and interesting sandwiches. I love their Turkish delight. You really can’t go wrong here. It’s a great sandwich shop and they have amazing chocolate cake and dill pickle chips. I come here every other Sunday for lunch.
Best. Sandwiches. Ever.
Great sandwich

Some of the best sandwiches around. So far the Ultimate Warrior is my favorite but you can't wrong with any choice. The country market feel is a very nice touch. It's also the perfect between Other Half and Sevdale breweries.
Fantastic! Best Reuben I’ve ever had!
I've been in opposition to giving this place a go because the sandwiches are pricey in my opinion. My fiancé got these less pricey breakfast ones and they were worth it. Really great tasting.!
Game-changing amazing all of the adjectives
(Translated by Google) Msandeuches  (Original) Msandeuches
Nice selections of sandwiches, the wait and prices keep it from 5 Star
Delicious breakfast and deli sandwiches and pricey but high-quality provisions like hot sauces, candies.

Decents overpriced sandwiches but my review is about the products and bakery/pastries they sell. For that it's a solid 2 stars as you never know when you're gonna buy bakery if it's fresh from the day or from the days before... Not to mention the sellers are really upset all the time.
Come here often and usually try a new sandwich each time. So far the ultimate warrior is my favorite.
Fantastic.  Great sandwiches
Best tomato sandwich EVER!

I love this place. I don't live or work anywhere near here but I'd come by for the sandwiches. Delicious, fresh and filling. My goal is to run through the entire menu. The Cubano is insane, and the Italian combo was heaven to my taste buds.
Love everything about this place
Macho Man sandwich is great!
Always a great experience when I come (food wise) place is small but food is big love every sandwich I get from here.. machoman is my go to sandwich btw

I have to say, the sandwiches here are beyond Amazing.  I’ve had the Cuban Sandwich,  Ruben with broccoli sandwich and the Ruben sandwich with corned beef and short rib.  Everyone of them were so good.  I LOVE this place.  They never ever disappoint me!  Can’t wait to try again.
Great sandwiches.
I got one of the veggie sandwiches. I've already raved about it to 5 people!
Decent store for basic daily needs...

One of the best corned beef sandwiches i have ever had. May not be super traditional marble rye, but the sandwiches are going to be gone in a few bites! Staff was beyond cool and not in a snobby, exclusive way. They have a dining room area past the sandwich counter. They also have coffee espresso and pastries, but not a huge grocery selection.
Nice selection of fine products.  Very nice staff
The Italian combo is all that

This place is amazing. Best sandwiches in Brooklyn, delicious fresh pastries, grumpy service that warms up when you need them to, and a great selection of specialty sundries. Tables are limited and wait times are long, but they take tap to pay to keep things moving.
Best hangover brunch sandwiches!
The vegitalian combo was one of the best veggie sandwiches I've ever had! Great spot!
I think I saw Lena Dunham here once.
My Favorite Cafe in the neighborhood, nice coffee, tea and great selection of Sandwiches!
Here, they serve the sandwich that you've been dreaming about. It's simply the best. Nothing much more I can add except to urge one to go early, and often to eat the sandwiches here.
The best Sandwiches
Great food

I love this place. Fantastic sammy's, good coffee, and nice vibes. It does feel a bit like store you would see in a Netflix original about some 40' somethings based in Cobble Hill, living in fantastic apartments and working high end jobs that they never have to be at. Like this is the place where the sensible one of the group goes to after he bumps into his old college sweat heart and has to dish it to his best friend before he starts acting unsensible and out of character and realizes he never really loved Megan the way he loved Amy. Any way, get "the ollie" it''s great.
great place and good food
Absolutely fantastic location. The best options. My number one place for a snack

brilliant! Of course, it's low key and not fancy at all, but the generosity and passion that the owners put in every detail is simply awesome. The homemade juniper soda steals the show. excellent music: sister sledge, McFadden and whitehead, soul classics and hidden gems. Surprisingly peaceful at brunchtime. A great place to bring your family, your friends, your crush. You'll remember it.

Good sandwich. Unfortunately, typical service from people who don’t understand the word Hospitality. You’re not doing me a favor, and if you only give service to who’s “cool” in your book, your just another entitled millennial.
killer sandwiches! great snacks.
All the sandwiches make me such a happy fat boy.
great food!!
The best sandwich shop in the area. They make their own meats and are known for their egg sandwich.
Yummy sandwich :-) 30 minute wait for that yummy sandwich :-(
Great sandwiches!

Best breakfast sandwiches around. Went in after an Other Half beer pick-up, and the women behind the counter were super friendly. I think we caught them on a low-key day, so it wasn't too crazy, and we're happy to chat with us. Vibe inside is cool, and I plan on going back soon for a lunch sandwich.
Best sandwichs ever!!! A bit expensive, but the food is totally worth it. I want to try them all hehe
Oh man, if you haven't been here for a sandwich. You. Are. Missing. Out!
Yo CSG. Where is your incredible summer tomato sandwich? Its 8/4/18 and it's still not available, and I am sad. Please halp. Thanks.

Super nice staff. B&B is one of the best breakfast sandwiches I've ever had. Other sandwiches are pricey ($10-$13) but packed to the brim with good meat and ingredients and delicious (had the Jawn this past weekend and can highly recommend). CSG has expanded across the city recently but this still feels like a neighborhood spot, one I keep coming back to.

Small hole n the wall restaurant with 2 sides, a deli style/takeout and a cafe style restaurant with table service. Delicious sandwiches with a Philadelphia flavor. Features theme sandwiches like "The Jawn".  😄 Great gluten free options including fresh baked bread and triple fudge cookies. You can also buy specialty items at the deli such as Kim Chi or exotic hot sauces.
Best sandwiches ive had in awhile. A whole menu of interesting options!
Best sandwiches, excruciating wait.

Man...that B&B is the best breakfast sandwich I've ever had.  This place is the spot to go on weekends before rush hour. It's a little tight inside, which is why you have to go before the rush or at off-times, but it's a dope place. Cool grocery part of it, too.  Very chill as you can order and eat, then pay after.  You gotta try it.
Best sandwich spot in the area.  Highly recommend.
The best sandwiches in Brooklyn.
Best sandwiches in the area. Bit of a wait typically.
wish there were more veggie sandwich options, but I know it's not that kind of place. still a little something for every taste and diet. lots of random awesome snacks.

SANDWICHES. So many amazing sandwiches. I never thought I would go broke from a sandwich habit, but here I am. Now I don't even think twice about spending 12-15 dollars on lunch. Somebody help me budget my life
The best sandwiches in Brooklyn.
Get in there and order a Droopy or Vegitalian...Stat.
Great sandwiches!
Relaxed location, delicious inventive sandwiches.
Personally, I chose to get a sandwich on my visit to Court Street Grocers!
B&B is the best breakfast sandwich ever. I said it.
nice store

The back of the house was very professional and efficient. The Jamaican lady working the register was downright NASTY not once but twice. I also  don't like all the DON'T POUR YOUR COFFEE HERE, WE KNOW THE WIFI IS SLOW signs. Remember we are customers not inmates.
The veg classic is the best veggie burger ever! And gluten free!

Ahh this place is golden. If only there was more veggie options. It’s also not cheap but the food is really good. It’s in such a cute little storefront too. Also recommend getting any of the baked goods. 🙌🏼
Ex-mother in law sandwich with beef short rib, kim chi and broccoli. Holy s*** so good and only $12
Very good sandwiches.

I normally don’t write reviews, but I have to for this place! I Randomly stopped by this place for a cup of coffee and fall in love with their Brownies!! It’s just so amazing.  I went back there just for the brownies. Will try their sandwich one day.
Tasty subs if a hair too precious. Would go back again though
Great place, great food
Delicious but pricey, with a solid selection of unique and hard to find items, like condiments, alternative milks, specialty sauces and more.
Great sandwiches. Horrible wait. Order ahead.
Turkey Club $13.06
Sandwiches are phenomenal. Coffee is on point. Groceries are random but occasionally exactly what you need.
Great all day breakfast sandwiches!!!

I've been going to this place since it first opened and they have the most amazing sandwich combinations and wonderful gluten-free focaccia bread that they can make any sandwich on! My go-to is The-Mother-In-Law that uses braised short rib, kimchi and broccoli rabe. They also have a fantastic assortment of sodas and Zapps chips that really make for the perfect lunch meal!
so good. smiling sandwiches, never dry 👌 also really good chips. i recommend the cajun dill gator tators 🐊
great sendwutches
Get the Mother in law. It's stupid Good!
Best sandwiches in Brooklyn!

Overpriced breakfast sandwich.. Arugula, egg and cheese for $7, should have gone to a bodega for a more filling/cheaper option. Wifi does not work here at all...part of the reason the experience lacked.
My hubby loves this place and took me here after his work shift once. I now know why. Thanks for the gluten free bread option ❤️

A friend of mine introduced me to this place.  As soon as I walked in, I felt like she had found a hidden gem.  We went to the back and ordered our sandwiches and then went into the adjoining room to wait for our order.  Almost instantly the place filled up.  Not so hidden after all.  As we walked out, I noticed it sells vintage candy including black licorice pipes.  I haven't seen those since Santa used to put them in my stocking.  I will definitely be coming back.  The Come Back Sauce worked!
(Translated by Google) Delicious sandwiches, if you are by Court comes for a hearty breakfast.  (Original) Sandwiches riquísimos, si estas por Court entra por un desayuno contundente.
Soooo delicious
Simply perfect breakfast sandwiches.
Delicious sandwiches!
great place, nice seating area, polite workers, food is made quick and neat, i got the ruben and grilled cheese sandwich, delicious, only thing...too unpleasantly oily/greasy
It's simple, superb sandwiches. Nuff said.
Vegetalian's are what dreams are made of.
If you're a meat lover then I highly recommend getting the Cuban sandwich! Their sandwiches are all great, but I definitely felt a ton of flavor bursting from the Cuban sandwich!
Holding out for a Hero(Sandwich). Yummy.
Great food and unique selection of food stuffs to buy. The mail draw is the sandwiches.

The tom yum was full of veggies and chicken and had substance. Best I've had to date. The broth is somehow thicker than the watery/oily tom yums with one meatball and few veggies I've had before in Boston. It's not overly spicy and had actually lemongrass stems in the broth.
Best breakfast sandwiches in Carroll Gardens!
Great sandwiches nice worker's
The sandwiches are amazing.
Best sandwiches and friendly service
Their "mother in law" sandwich is amazing!
Amazing food and friendly staff. They are always so nice when I go in there! Absolutely love this place.
Best breakfast sandwich. Macho Man is pretty dope too.
Best deli in the world. Super sandwiches, delicious coffee, good staff.
Good coffee
Great Reuben!
Really good Reuben. Pretty quick.
Awesome sandwiches...
Fantastic premium sandwiches. Can't go wrong with anything here. Lines can be a bit long but it's worth the wait.
Amazing food, decent dining room for a quick bite.
Best sandwich shop in Brooklyn hands down.
Great food and friendly staff, no decaf coffee but otherwise peaceful experience

Great place for delicious breakfast sandwiches. Order your sandwich, then claim a seat at one of ten tables in the back. They also have amazing baked goods as well as a few shelves containing a random assortment of dry goods for purchase.
Great sandwiches and a nice selection of packaged goods.

A well-done mashup of a small-town market, a WiFi coffeehouse where loitering is acceptible, and a gourmet deli with premium, organic ingredients - standard fare at gold-standard flavor and specials that are simultaneously haute-cuisine and comfort food. Every nook and cranny offers a curious sight - both in the place's selection of curious goods, and also in odd artifacts added to the decor by either patrons or staff.  The fifth star is withheld only because for all of it's well-currated charm, it is pricey and cramped. This particular location is off the beaten path - equidiatant from both nearest F/G stops - making it evidently not part of the commons of Brooklyn foot traffic, but instead, a "destination" for those seeking a rustic experience and tailored to a crowd who either happens to live nearby or who can drive to indulge in that sort of well-groomed luxury.
Delicious sandwiches.

Amazing sandwiches and a great atmosphere. I got the veggie combo with roasted butternut squash and cheese. Amazing! Also they had Zapp's chips from New Orleans and Cafe du Monde beignet mix which I picked up to take home as well.

Great sandwiches. Anything on a hero will be massive, so bring an appetite or a friend to help. Awesome breakfast selection too. Really friendly and chill staff. A small selection of gourmet dry goods and an even smaller collection of fresh groceries (eggs, fresh noodles, dairy) but rarely any produce. There is a good amount of seating but this place is massively popular on the weekend so be prepared for a packed house. Free wifi makes a great place to work, but the music selection is eclectic so may not be conducive to productivity depending on what's playing. Love this place so much!
So good. So unique. Don't be fearful of the mother-in-law at this place.

A great neighborhood spot with creative, reasonably-priced, made-to-order sandwiches in the back. Peruse the wide selection of somewhat expensive condiments on the shelves, and then grab some hot coffee, Four and Twenty Blackbirds pie, and fresh salads and sides in front.  Favorite sandwiches: Mother-in-Law (with house braised beef short rib), Mr. Victor, Broccoli Reuben, and Uncle Chucky.
People usually underestimate their baked goods, which are usually amazing. In my opinion, their ruggelach is the best in NYC.
A bit pricey but awesome sandwiches
Amazing Ruben's delicious B+B breakfast sandwiches. Certainly a home run. Even on an off day. Yum

Court Street has some of the tastiest sandwiches in the city all in what looks like a corner grocery store. In front, there are shelves of snacks and drinks from around the world including interesting products not normally sold in the US. Behind the counter though is a second counter for sandwiches. There aren’t a huge number of choices, but the ones there are delicious. The macho man comes on a toasted garlic bread with deliciously marinated pork shoulder and pickled jalapeno. The bread is crispy and perfect, holding up to the sloppy ingredients well. The meat is also delicious and flavorful. The space itself isn’t incredibly atmospheric, but it works for shoving down the delicious sandwiches.

One of my favorite delis to visit for both breakfast and lunch. If you're in the mood for a really tasty sandwich, you'll want to go here. Crunchy breads and not too much meat. Love the Italian combo.
The Macho sandwich is amazing!!!

There's a lot of hype around their sandwiches, and while each is an inventive mix of ingredients, we found them to be a bit underwhelming. Maybe we came on an off day, but the ingredients didn't seem as premium or well-prepared as expected. I'd certainly give them another chance, but (in my opinion) this place wasn't a home run.

Walking in, the place is split into two parts. One side is service and the other is seating.  Walk past the register, some random assortment of sauce, hot sauce, ethnic groceries, and there is a sandwich counter where you order.  I went with the pulled pork sandwich duck sauce. The bread was fresh with a crunchy crush and a soft middle, like a ciabatta. The pulled pork was flavorful and the sweetness of the sauce really complemented the meat. However, the portion was a bit small for $9+, including tax. (For comparison, Mighty Quinns charges $7.25 for a much larger sandwich).  Still a great place to eat before going to Other Half Brewing. I'm curious to see how their other sandwiches turn out, even though they are priced towards $10+.
Best breakfast sandwich in Brooklyn
One of the best sandwiches I ever had.
The sandwiches here never fail. When I was eating meat I would dream of the Italian and now that I've stopped the Uncle Chucky fills my fantasies. And THE BREAD.

We stopped by for breakfast at Gotham West Market. The egg sandwich might be the best one in the entire city-salty cabot cheddar, perfectly scrambled eggs, and arugula on a soft ciabatta roll. It was absolutely fantastic.
If you're looking for the ultimate breakfast sandwich, you've definitely come to the right place. You MUST get the Mr. Victor if you're a sausage fan.
The Reuben is great, but the Delight is even better.

Sandwiches, prepared foods and lots of fun groceries. The only thing i don't like about it is that it's pretty expensive. That said, I think the quality is worth the splurge. They even have a seating area where you can enjoy your purchases, which is nice if you're not looking to take your food "to-go."
Have yet to not have an amazing sandwich here. The staff is very friendly and you can tell the owners cafe about their customers.

This is the perfect neighborhood grocery. You won't do your weekly shopping here, but you'll find yourself back again and again for the amazing sandwiches, the highly curated but somehow relaxed, genuine, and small-town-ish selection of grocery items, and the great selection of 90's tunes. Support shopkeeping done right and patronize this place on the regular.

Produce here is especially outstanding - fresh and plentifully stocked. Flower selection is also extensive. Easy to find most grocery basics, though if I'm really cooking something detailed, there's almost always at least an item or two I can't find here. Very friendly workers.
Some of the very best sandwiches I've ever had, from really nice people. The $12 turkey club -- repriced from $10 because they "did the math" -- is worth every penny.
